Description:
What?
User will be logging in to the application with login credentials. 

In case, the credentials are not valid, the user will be redirected to login page with valid message displayed for login attempt failure.

In case user is not having credentials, user will be able to register. Hence, a link will be given to re-direct the user to registration page.

In case of successful login attempt, user will be redirected to user specific home page.

Why?
In order to access the application and features, the user will be logged in first.

Where?
Login page.

When?
HeartiHealth\Sprint 1 - UAT

Who?
All application users.

How?
User will be able to fill credential details in following:
  1. Email
  2. Password
User will be able to submit the details through "Login" button.

In case the user is not having the credentials, provide the following section with message "Not Registered? Register Here". "Register Here" will work as link to redirect the user to registration page.

User will be given with a link named as "Forgot Password" to redirect the user to reset password page, in case user forgot the password.

Rules:​

UI Rules:
  1. Email field will be a text field with email only restriction.
  2. Password field will be a text field with hide password with star(*) validation on typing.
Login attempt failure message corresponding to related field: "Incorrect Email/Password".

Format validation message corresponding to related field: "Incorrect Email/Password Format".

PFA wire frame for reference.

Data Rules:
  1. Email ID should be unique.
  2. Password should contain special characters.

What?
User can logout at any point while browsing through the application.

Once the user logs out of the application, he/she will be redirected to the login page.

Why?
Once user is finished browsing the application, he/she can logout in order to release the access from the portal.

Where?
Top right corner of Navigation Bar.

When?
HeartiHealth\Sprint 1 - UAT

Who?
All application users.

How?
User will be able to logout from the application with a "Logout" button given at top right corner of navigation bar.

Rules:​

UI Rules:
User should have access to the "Logout" button at any point of time, while browsing through the application.

PFA wire frame for reference.

What?
User will register into the application with given set of fields to save user details.

Why?
In case user will not have the login credentials, the user will submit the personal details and have the credentials created.

Where?
From Login Page

When?
HeartiHealth\Sprint 1 - UAT

Who?
All application users.

How?
User will be able to fill following details:
  1. Email 
  2. User Name
  3. Password
  4. Re-enter Password
User will be able to submit the details with "Register" button. Once successful submission, user should be redirected to Login Page.

In case the user is having login credentials, a section with message "Already Registered? Log In Now". "Log In Now" will work as link, redirecting user to Login Screen.

Rules:​

UI Rules:
  1. Email field will be a text field with email only restriction.
  2. User Name should be a text field, without any special characters.
  3. Password/Re-enter Password field will be a text field with hide password with star(*) validation on typing.
Format validation message corresponding to related field: "Incorrect Email/Password Format".

PFA wire frame for reference.

Data Rules:
  1. Email ID should be unique.
  2. Username should be unique and should not contain special characters.
  3. Password should contain special characters.

Title 3: Registration - Email Notification on Registration Confirmation
Description:
What?
User will receive an email notification after successfully registering into the application.

Why?
In order to notify user with registered email with the login credentials.

Where?
Registration Screen

When?
HeartiHealth\Sprint 1 - UAT

Who?
All application users.

How?
Once the user clicks "Register" from registration screen and the details are successfully saved into the system, an email notification will be sent to user with registered email ID.

Rules:​

UI Rules:

Email Subject: Hearti Health Credentials

Email Format:

Hi <Username>,

Greetings!

An account for your email ID is created, below are your credentials:

Username: <Username>

Password: <Password>

URL:  <Application URL>

Contact Information: <Contact Number> 

Kindly, reach out to <Support email id>  in case of any queries.

Stay Fit! Stay Healthy!

Regards,
Hearti Health Team

Data Rules:
  1. Registration information should be saved successfully.
  2. Valid email ID should be used for email notification.

Response Time - Response Turn Around Time w.r.t. Load
Description:
What?
The turn around time for a response on any request from the application will be measured and 
will fall under the benchmark set for TAT w.r.t. Load.

Why?
In order to set benchmark, measure, log inconsistencies and fixes for the TAT w.r.t. load on the application.

Where?
Whole Application.

When?
HeartiHealth\Sprint 1 - UAT

Who?
Automated Load of Users.

How?
An automated load of users in the ratio 1:10:100 (Concurrent:Active:Total) will be using the application, covering following areas:
  1. Login
  2. Registration
  3. Dashboard
  4. Predictor
  5. Predictor Results
Current Concurrent Users as an Automated Load on Application: 500

Benchmark TAT for Response : 2-3 Secs

What?
All the modules in the application will be Google Chrome browser compatible.

Why?
Being a web-application, the product should work flawlessly, with features having compatible and expected functionalities in the browser.

Where?
Entire Application

When?
HeartiHealth\Sprint 1 - UAT

Who?
All application users.

How?
A feature wise browser compatible testing will be done for each user role and the functionalities for each feature will be checked.

All the modules and features will be listed and expected benchmark and actual benchmark success rate will be defined for each feature/sub-feature.
